.TH FINDINSTALLAPP "1" "December 2025" "findInstallApp 202304121238-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
findInstallApp \- Intelligent application finder and installer using multiple package managers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B findInstallApp
[\fI\,PACKAGE\fR]... [\fI\,OPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B findInstallApp
is an intelligent application installation helper that automatically searches for and installs packages using multiple package management systems. It tries package managers in order (pkmgr, dfmgr, systemmgr, npm) until the application is successfully installed or all managers have been attempted.
.PP
The script features graphical progress dialogs (zenity) when running in a desktop environment, automatic fallback between package managers, sudo privilege verification, and internet connectivity checking. It simplifies package installation by abstracting away which package manager contains the desired application.
.PP
findInstallApp is particularly useful for installing packages when you're unsure which package manager contains them, for automated installation scripts that work across different system configurations, and for providing user-friendly GUI installation experiences with progress feedback.
.SH USAGE
.B findInstallApp
