.SH PACKAGE MANAGER ORDER
findInstallApp tries package managers in this order until successful:
.SS Priority Order
.RS
.IP 1. 3
pkmgr - Primary package manager wrapper
.IP 2. 3
dfmgr - Dotfiles manager for configuration packages
.IP 3. 3
systemmgr - System-level package manager (requires sudo)
.IP 4. 3
npm - Node Package Manager for JavaScript packages
.RE
.SS Manager Selection Logic
.RS
.EX
if pkmgr install <pkg> succeeds: done
else if dfmgr install <pkg> succeeds: done
else if systemmgr install <pkg> succeeds: done
else if npm install -g <pkg> succeeds: done
else: installation failed
.EE
.RE
