.SH INSTALLATION PROCESS
How findInstallApp works internally:
.SS Pre-Installation Checks
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Verify internet connectivity (curl to 1.1.1.1)
.IP 2. 3
Check if package is already installed (__cmd_exists)
.IP 3. 3
Verify sudo privileges if required
.IP 4. 3
Ensure bash is available
.RE
.SS Manager Attempts
.RS
For each package:
.EX
For pkg in package_list:
  If already installed: skip
  Else:
    Try pkmgr install pkg
    If failed: try dfmgr install pkg
    If failed: try systemmgr install pkg
    If failed: try npm install -g pkg
    If all failed: report error
.EE
.RE
.SS Success Criteria
.RS
.IP \\(bu 2
Package command exists after installation
.IP \\(bu 2
Installation exit code is 0
.IP \\(bu 2
No errors reported by package manager
.RE
